     </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2"> This deck uses a nigh invincible fellowship that heals every maneuver phase with a swarm deck that just seems never to end.<br />
<br />
 Fellowship Strategy<br />
<br />
Bid 4-6 and go first exert to pull Aragorn out of your deck but only move to site 2 if your opponent plays a minion they will have to fight 2 8 strength characters if you use Legolas, pretty hefty thing to do. Just move 1 site each turn taking your time and healing. If your opponent gets a minion through your archery they will be hacked down by your strong and fresh fellowship. But becareful with Eomer you can only heal him at a Sanctuary. When you reach site 7 race to 9 I can guarantee that your opponent will not be to far ahead of you. Remember the deck is built around winning with the shadow so don&#39;t worry if you are a little behind. Big note you don&#39;t need to wound everything put a wound on a minion skirmishing Eomer with Firefoot and they are chopped liver in seconds.<br />
<br />
<br />
 Shadow Strategy<br />
<br />
Swarm, Swarm, Swarm. With this deck it is possible to swarm your opponent before site 3 and who can stand up to a site 2 Cave Troll. The key to this deck is to remember that most of your minions cost little or no twilight and some add to your twilight. Also remember keep drawing cards the more cards in your hands the more minions you can play. And just picture when you play a free Balrog with Power and Terror than follow it up with a Cave Troll and tons of little Goblins. One Key Rule to using this deck though is never goof off or play with an opponent. Swarm Frodo the bloody little munchkin and Swarm him good. Enjoy the deck.<br />
 <br />
 Zak Cardwell </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
